import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    
    ax.hist(data['US_Gross'], alpha=0.5, label='US_Gross', color='blue', bins=20)
    ax.hist(data['Worldwide_Gross'], alpha=0.5, label='Worldwide_Gross', color='green', bins=20)
    
    ax.set_xlabel('Gross Revenue')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?')
    ax.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['Production_Budget'], data['US_Gross'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Production Budget')
    ax.set_ylabel('US Gross')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between Production_Budget and US_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'], alpha=0.5, label='Rotten Tomatoes Rating', color='blue')
    plt.hist(data['IMDB_Rating'] * 10, alpha=0.5, label='IMDB Rating (Scaled)', color='green')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Rating')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Running_Time_min'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Running Time')
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['Running_Time_min'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    mpaa_genre_counts = data.groupby(['MPAA_Rating', 'Major_Genre']).size().unstack()
    ax = mpaa_genre_counts.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating and Major_Genre?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("MPAA Rating")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Movies")
    plt.legend(title="Major Genre", loc="upper right")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
